A 180-page comparative study analyzing traditional and sustainable agricultural practices. The study assesses the environmental, economic, and social impacts of various practices, including organic farming, crop rotation, and the use of biotechnology in agriculture. The document addresses the challenges of implementing sustainable agriculture on a large scale, its role in ensuring food security, and the impact of climate change on agricultural trends. It includes global case studies illustrating the successful implementation of sustainable methods and discusses the economic viability of these practices in the face of global market shifts and technological advancements.